<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Privacy Policy - Monkeytype</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        color: beige;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
        background: #333;
      }

      h1,
      h2,
      h3 {
        text-align: center;
        animation: fadeInDown 1s ease;
      }

      h2 {
        margin-top: 50px;
        color: yellow;
      }

      ul.toc {
        list-style-type: none;
        padding-left: 0;
        background: none;
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 15px;
      }

      ul.toc li {
        padding: 10px 0;
        list-style-type: decimal;
      }

      ul.toc a {
        text-decoration: none;
        color: yellow;
      }

      ul.toc a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }

      section {
        margin-top: 30px;
      }

      @keyframes fadeInDown {
        from {
          opacity: 0;
          transform: translateY(-20px);
        }
        to {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: translateY(0);
        }
      }

      @media (max-width: 400px) {
        body {
          padding: 10px;
          font-size: 0.95em;
        }

        ul.toc li {
          padding: 8px 0;
        }
      }
      h1 {
        color: yellow;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      <strong>Effective date:</strong> April 26, 2025<br />
      <strong>Last updated:</strong> May 02 2025
    </p>

    <p>
      Thanks for trusting <em style="color: yellow">Kihsotype</em> with your
      personal information...
    </p>

    <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
    <ul class="toc">
      <li><a href="#data-collect">What data do we collect?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#collect-methods">How do we collect your data?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#data-use">How will we use your data?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#data-storage">How do we store your data?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#rights">What are your data protection rights?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#log-data">What log data do we collect?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#ads">Advertisements</a></li>
      <li><a href="#ads-2">Advertisements Part 2</a></li>
      <li><a href="#cookies">What are cookies?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#use-cookies">How do we use cookies?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#cookie-types">What types of cookies do we use?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#manage-cookies">How to manage your cookies</a></li>
      <li>
        <a href="#external-policies">Privacy policies of other websites</a>
      </li>
      <li><a href="#policy-changes">Changes to our privacy policy</a></li>
      <li><a href="#contact">How to contact us</a></li>
    </ul>

    <section id="data-collect">
      <h2>What data do we collect?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Email</li>
        <li>Username</li>
        <li>Discord ID and avatar ID</li>
        <li>Typing test data</li>
        <li>Active settings</li>
        <li>Test counts and duration</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do NOT collect custom texts stored locally.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="collect-methods">
      <h2>How do we collect your data?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Creating an account</li>
        <li>Completing typing tests</li>
        <li>Changing settings</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="data-use">
      <h2>How will we use your data?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Show result history</li>
        <li>Save results and show stats</li>
        <li>Remember settings</li>
        <li>Display leaderboards</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="data-storage">
      <h2>How do we store your data?</h2>
      <p>We use MongoDB for secure storage.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="rights">
      <h2>What are your data protection rights?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Access</li>
        <li>Rectification</li>
        <li>Erasure (with conditions)</li>
        <li>Restrict processing</li>
        <li>Object to processing</li>
        <li>Data portability</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="log-data">
      <h2>What log data do we collect?</h2>
      <p>
        Standard log data like IP address, browser, ISP, etc., via Google
        Analytics.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="ads">
      <h2>Advertisements</h2>
      <p>Optional ads via Playwire with consent form (CMP).</p>
    </section>

    <section id="ads-2">
      <h2>Advertisements Part 2</h2>
      <p>Common ID cookie and settings for EU users.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="cookies">
      <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
      <p>Text files used for tracking and improving user experience.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="use-cookies">
      <h2>How do we use cookies?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Sign-in persistence</li>
        <li>Save settings and tags</li>
        <li>Traffic and ad analysis</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="cookie-types">
      <h2>What types of cookies do we use?</h2>
      <p>Functionality cookies only.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="manage-cookies">
      <h2>How to manage your cookies</h2>
      <p>
        You can set your browser to refuse cookies, but some features may break.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="external-policies">
      <h2>Privacy policies of other websites</h2>
      <p>We link to external websites. Read their policies separately.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="policy-changes">
      <h2>Changes to our privacy policy</h2>
      <p>We regularly review and may change this policy without notice.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
      <h2>How to contact us</h2>
      <p>
        Email: kihsogaming@gmail.com<br />
        Ads:
        <a
          href="https://www.playwire.com/contact-direct-sales"
          style="color: yellow"
          target="_blank"
          >Playwire contact page</a
        >
      </p>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>
